<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 01:05:12 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>了解肠道微生物酶在 CMD 中的作用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/understanding-the-role-of-gut-microbial-enzyme-in-cmd</link><description>近年来，肠道菌群与宿主心脏代谢疾病（CMD）（包括动脉粥样硬化、糖尿病和代谢功能障碍相关脂肪性肝炎（MASH））之间假定的功能关系的研究受到了前所未有的关注。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/understanding-the-role-of-gut-microbial-enzyme-in-cmd2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 01:05:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/understanding-the-role-of-gut-microbial-enzyme-in-cmd</guid></item><item><title>这些微生物可以在地球上最极端的环境中繁衍生息——甚至可能更远</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/these-microbes-can-thrive-in-the-most-extreme-environments-on-earth-and-maybe-beyond</link><description>极端微生物可能存在于冰冷的卫星和行星上，其条件类似于冰下水域或海底。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/these-microbes-can-thrive-in-the-most-extreme-environments-on-earth-and-maybe-beyond.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 00:50:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/these-microbes-can-thrive-in-the-most-extreme-environments-on-earth-and-maybe-beyond</guid></item><item><title>为什么肺部老化不均匀：脆弱细胞可能指导新疗法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/why-lungs-age-unevenly-vulnerable-cells-may-guide-new-therapies</link><description>衰老与几乎所有肺部疾病的风险增加有关，包括肺炎等急性疾病和慢性阻塞性肺病、特发性肺纤维化和肺癌等慢性疾病。现在，对人类肺部衰老最全面的分析之一发现，并非所有细胞的衰老程度相同。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-lungs-age-unevenly-vulnerable-cells-may-guide-new-therapies2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 00:35:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/why-lungs-age-unevenly-vulnerable-cells-may-guide-new-therapies</guid></item><item><title>为什么模拟整个细胞周期需要数年时间、多个 GPU 并且每次运行需要六天时间</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/why-simulating-an-entire-cell-cycle-took-years-multiple-gpus-and-six-days-per-run</link><description>通过模拟最小细菌细胞的生命周期（从 DNA 复制到蛋白质翻译，再到新陈代谢和细胞分裂），科学家们为计算机视觉研究生命的基本过程开辟了新领域。由伊利诺伊大学厄巴纳-香槟分校化学教授 Zan Luthey-Schulten 领导的研究人员介绍了&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-simulating-an-entire-cell-cycle-took-years-multiple-gpus-and-six-days-per-run2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 00:20:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/why-simulating-an-entire-cell-cycle-took-years-multiple-gpus-and-six-days-per-run</guid></item><item><title>锶光学钟在 300 亿年里精确到 1 秒以内</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/strontium-optical-clock-accurate-to-within-1-second-over-30-billion-years</link><description>中国科学技术大学的研究人员在光学时钟技术方面取得重大突破，研制出一种稳定性和不确定性均超过10⁻19水平的锶光学晶格时钟，这意味着该时钟在大约300亿年的时间里慢或快的时间不到一秒。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/strontium-optical-clock-accurate-to-within-1-second-over-30-billion-years.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 00:05:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/strontium-optical-clock-accurate-to-within-1-second-over-30-billion-years</guid></item><item><title>詹姆斯韦伯太空望远镜观察垂死恒星“暴露的头盖骨”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/jwst-peers-inside-a-dying-stars-exposed-cranium</link><description>正如《JWST》所揭示的那样，暴露的颅骨星云类似于宇宙大脑，但却显示出一颗垂死的大质量恒星。它的命运仍然不确定。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/jwst-peers-inside-a-dying-stars-exposed-cranium.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 23:50:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/jwst-peers-inside-a-dying-stars-exposed-cranium</guid></item><item><title>比特币的开采量达到 2000 万个里程碑，最后 100 万个 BTC 将在未来 114 年发行</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/bitcoins-mined-supply-hits-20-million-milestone-leaving-final-1-million-btc-to-be-issued-over-next-114-years</link><description>最后的 100 万枚 BTC 将需要一个多世纪的时间来开采，最后的一小部分（以聪为单位）预计将在 2140 年左右发行。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/bitcoins-mined-supply-hits-20-million-milestone-leaving-final-1-million-btc-to-be-issued-over-next-114-years.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 23:35:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/bitcoins-mined-supply-hits-20-million-milestone-leaving-final-1-million-btc-to-be-issued-over-next-114-years</guid></item><item><title>世界首例批准干细胞治疗帕金森病和心力衰竭</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/stem-cell-treatments-for-parkinsons-and-heart-failure-approved-in-world-first</link><description>日本已批准破土动工&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/stem-cell-treatments-for-parkinsons-and-heart-failure-approved-in-world-first.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 23:20:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/stem-cell-treatments-for-parkinsons-and-heart-failure-approved-in-world-first</guid></item><item><title>用于尖峰强化学习的非线性光子神经形态芯片</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nonlinear-photonic-neuromorphic-chips-for-spiking-reinforcement-learning</link><description>光子计算芯片在加速线性计算方面取得了重大进展，但非线性计算通常在数字域中实现，这引入了额外的系统延迟和功耗，并阻碍了全功能光子神经网络芯片的实现。在这里，我们提出并制造了一种16通道可编程非相干光子神经形态计算芯片，通过使用不同材料共同设计简化的马赫-曾德干涉仪（MZI）网格和具有可饱和吸收器（DFBs-SA）阵列的分布式反馈激光器，从而能够通过两个单独的芯片在光域中实现线性和非线性尖峰计算。此外，之前的研究主要集中在监督学习和简单的图像分类任务上。在这里，我们首先根据我们的知识和时间提出了光子尖峰强化学习（RL）架构，并开发了一个软件-硬件协作训练推理框架（原位光子训练和硬件感知微调）来解决训练尖峰强化学习模型的挑战。我们实现了整层光子尖峰强化学习的大规模、节能（光子线性计算：1.39 TOPS/W，光子非线性计算：987.65 GOPS/W）和低延迟（片上 320 ps）部署。基于尖峰近端策略优化 (PPO) 算法，通过实验演示了两个 RL 基准，包括离散 CartPole 任务和连续 Pendulum 任务。 CartPole (Pendulum) 任务的软硬件协同计算奖励值分别收敛到 200 (−250)，与传统的 PPO 算法相当。该实验演示解决了缺乏大规模片上光子非线性尖峰计算和尖峰强化学习训练困难的挑战，提出了一种高速、低延迟的光子尖峰强化学习解决方案，在机器人控制、自动驾驶和体现智能等领域具有广阔的应用前景。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nonlinear-photonic-neuromorphic-chips-for-spiking-reinforcement-learning.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 23:05:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nonlinear-photonic-neuromorphic-chips-for-spiking-reinforcement-learning</guid></item><item><title>实验室测试中抗癌药物可降低早期阿尔茨海默氏症样大脑过度连接</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cancer-drug-reduces-early-alzheimers-like-brain-hyperconnectivity-in-lab-tests</link><description>伦敦国王学院的神经科学家已经查明了在阿尔茨海默病早期阶段观察到的神经连接增强背后的机制。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cancer-drug-reduces-early-alzheimers-like-brain-hyperconnectivity-in-lab-tests3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 22:50:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cancer-drug-reduces-early-alzheimers-like-brain-hyperconnectivity-in-lab-tests</guid></item></channel></rss>